# SIEM Lab

This repository contains the setup and configuration files for a lab environment to study and experiment with Security Information and Event Management (SIEM) systems.

## Overview

This lab includes:
- Installing and configuring SIEM software.
- Deploying SIEM agents on endpoints.
- Collecting and analyzing logs.
- Creating and testing attack scenarios.

## Prerequisites

- VirtualBox or VMware Workstation
- Vagrant (if using Vagrant for VM management)
- SIEM software (e.g., Splunk, ELK stack)

## Setup Instructions

1. Clone this repository:
    ```sh
    git clone https://github.com/yourusername/SIEM-Lab.git
    cd SIEM-Lab
    ```

2. Follow the setup guides in the `Setup` directory to configure your lab environment.

